Facts (layer 2):

`transmute :: a -> b` (ConstantDefinition):
  has definition constraints
  has type `a -> a`
  has type parameters
  is a definition

`a` (TypeParameter):
  has type `a` or `b`
  is a definition
  is a type
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `a`

`a -> b` (FunctionType):
  has type `a -> a`
  is a type

`b` (TypeParameter):
  has type `a` or `b`
  is a definition
  is a type
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `b`

`transmute : x -> x` (AssignmentStatement):
  has type `()`

`x` (VariablePattern):
  has type `a` or `b`
  is a definition
  is a pattern

`x -> x` (FunctionExpression):
  has type `a -> a`
  is an expression

`x` (VariableExpression):
  has type `a` or `b`
  is an expression
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `x`



Feedback:

`x` (conflicting-types)

  `x` is a `a` or a `b`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `x` must be the same type as `x`, `a`, and `b`; double-check these.


`x` (conflicting-types)

  `x` is a `a` or a `b`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `x` must be the same type as `x`, `a`, and `b`; double-check these.


`a` (conflicting-types)

  `a` is a `a` or a `b`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `a` must be the same type as `x`, `x`, and `b`; double-check these.


`b` (conflicting-types)

  `b` is a `a` or a `b`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `b` must be the same type as `x`, `x`, and `a`; double-check these.
